<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-30T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-30T22:00:00-05:00" n="309" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d309">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W./8–3044: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé to the Greek Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Shantz</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Cairo</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-30T23:00:00-04:00">August
                                        30, 1944—11 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>77. You are authorized to concert with Lord Moyne in notifying the
                                Greek Government of the Bulgarian armistice terms, the text of which
                                is being sent separately.<note n="42" xml:id="d309fn42">Telegram 76,
                                    August 30, 10 p.m., not printed.</note> See in this connection
                                the Department’s telegram to London,<note n="43" xml:id="d309fn43">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> repeated to you, concerning
                                the procedure for notification of all other Governments at war with
                                Bulgaria.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>